        <h2>Introduction :</h2>
                            <p>
                                After your 10th Board Exams, choosing the appropriate stream has a significant 
                                impact on your future and professional path. It’s that phase in your career 
                                where parents and pupils are equally anxious and full of joy. The student’s 
                                chosen stream significantly influences the student’s further studies and career 
                                opportunities. Here’s the guide that can help you make an informed decision. 
                            </p>
        
        <h2>The Importance of This Decision</h2>                    
                            <p>
                                The choice of stream after the 10th Board Exams is not just about the subjects 
                                you’ll study for the next two years, but it will surely lay the foundation 
                                stone for your career and hopefully your bright future. This decision determines 
                                courses that will be available to you in college, and your career opportunities that 
                                ultimately will decide how fruitful will your professional life will be. To make sure 
                                that your education matches your interests and professional goals, you must make an 
                                informed decision.
                            </p>

        <h2>Understanding the Streams</h2>
                    <p>
                        Following the 10th Board Exams, students typically select from one of three following main streams.
                    </p>

        <h3>1. Science:</h3>  
                <p>This is the perfect stream for those students interested in subjects like Physics, 
                    Chemistry, Biology, and Mathematics. After completing their studies in this stream 
                    students can pursue jobs in engineering, research, medical, and other technology-related 
                    fields.
                </p>         

        <h3>2. Commerce:</h3>
                <p>
                    If students are interested in accounting, business, finance, or economics they should 
                    take this stream. Students completing their studies in this stream can find work 
                    opportunities in chartered accounting, banking, business management, and economics.
                </p>

        <h3>3. Humanities (Arts):</h3>        
                <p>
                    Students who want to make their careers in creative industries, and have an interest 
                    in subjects like psychology, sociology, history, geography, or education can think 
                    about this stream.
                </p>

        <h2>Factors to Consider While Choosing a Stream</h2>

        <h3>1.Interest and Passion:</h3>        
                <p>
                    Choose a stream that matches your interests. You will most likely succeed in a 
                    subject if you are very interested.
                </p>

        <h3>2. Strengths and Weaknesses:</h3>        
                <p>
                    After identifying your deficiencies, pick a stream that most effectively highlights your strengths.
                </p>

        <h3>3. Career Goals:</h3>
                <p>
                    Keep an eye on the big picture while considering professional objectives. Do extensive 
                    study on the criteria to ensure that the stream you select meets the requirements for 
                    the career you are interested in.
                </p>

        <h3>4. Performance in 10th Board Exams:</h3>
                <p>
                    More than your grade, your performance on the Xth Board Exam will demonstrate the subjects 
                    you are passionate about and have the capacity to excel in. Your grades should not be the 
                    sole consideration, even though they should be used as a reference.
                </p>

        <h2>Vocational Stream</h2>
                <p>Apart from the traditional streams, after Xth Board Exams vocational education is also a 
                    viable option. It means providing hands-on training in particular sectors, such as 
                    computer technology, hospitality, and tourism, which results in job openings or more 
                    specialised education.
                </p>

        <h2>Seeking Guidance from School Counsellors</h2>
                <p>
                    After the 10th Board Exams, school counsellors are crucial in assisting applicants in 
                    selecting the appropriate career. They could help you by offering you enlightening details 
                    about each stream, having a conversation with oneself about abilities and interests, and 
                    suggesting a career path according to your aptitudes.
                </p>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                <p>
                    After your 10th Board Exams, selecting the appropriate course is crucial because it will 
                    affect your future. The best thing to do after the 10th exam is to do your research in each 
                    stream, assess your abilities and interests and seek guidance from school counsellors. 
                    Always remember that this is a significant decision, and consider all of your options 
                    carefully and thoughtfully to make sure you select a path that leads to professional and 
                    personal happiness.
                </p>

        <h1 style="text-align: center;">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

            <h3>Q1: What to do if you have chosen the wrong stream?</h3>
                <p>
                    A1: No issues, it’s ok to feel uncertain. Many students after choosing the right stream 
                    realise their passion lies elsewhere and switch streams later. It is necessary to have a 
                    free conversation with teachers and counsellors to find a solution that works for the 
                    student.
                </p>

            <h3>Q2: Is it possible to change streams after the 11th Grade?</h3>
                <p>
                    A2: Yes, several colleges allow their students to switch streams after the 11th grade. However,
                    it’s advisable to make an informed decision before only to avoid the hassle of switching.
                </p>

            <h3>Q3: How is the stream decided in Class 10?</h3>
                <p>
                    A3: Though marks can be an indicator of your strengths, it should not be the sole factor. 
                    Interest and passion in the subjects are equally important for the student.
                </p>

            <h3>Q4: Is there a test to help you choose the right stream after the 10th?</h3>
                <p>
                    A4: Yes, many schools and educational institutions offer aptitude tests to help students 
                    identify their strengths and interests can be extremely helpful for them in making a 
                    decision.
                </p>
